-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/ghana-s-cocoa-board-gets-banker-bids-for-2-billion-trade-finance-facility.html
The Ghana Cocoa Board is receiving
bids from banks for a $2 billion trade-financing facility for
cocoa purchases in the current year and the next crop year,
Deputy Chief Executive Officer Yaw Adu-Ampomah said.  The board is seeking $500 million more than it did last
year for the purchases, Adu-Ampomah said in a phone interview
today from Accra, the capital.  The has purchased 713,000 metric tons of  cocoa beans  from
farmers in the first 22 weeks of the current season that began
in October, compared with about 400,000 in the same period a
year earlier, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
